# OTP Input — Styles

CSS file: `@acko/css/otp-input.css`

## Class structure
- `.acko-otp` — flex row, `gap: var(--scale-8)`
- `.acko-otp-cell` — individual input, `text-center font-semibold outline-none`, `border: 1.5px solid var(--color-input-border)`, `background: var(--color-input-bg)`, `color: var(--color-text-default)`, `caret-color: var(--color-primary)`, `::selection: --color-primary-subtle`
- `.acko-otp-cell-filled` — `border-color: var(--color-input-filled-border)`, `background: var(--color-primary-subtle)`, `color: var(--color-primary)`
- `.acko-otp-cell-error` — gradient border via `background` + `border-box` trick
- `.acko-otp-disabled` — parent class; `.acko-otp-disabled .acko-otp-cell` gets disabled styling

## Size classes — perfect squares with per-size radius

| Class | Cell size | Font | Border Radius |
|-------|-----------|------|---------------|
| `.acko-otp-sm` | `40×40` (`--scale-40`) | `--font-body-md-size` | `12px` (`--radius-2xl`) |
| `.acko-otp-md` | `48×48` (`--scale-48`) | `--font-heading-md-size` | `16px` (`--radius-3xl`) |
| `.acko-otp-lg` | `56×56` (`--scale-56`) | `--font-heading-lg-size` | `20px` (raw) |

## States
- **Default**: `border-color: var(--color-input-border)`, `background: var(--color-input-bg)`, `color: var(--color-text-default)`
- **Focus**: `border-color: var(--color-input-focus-border)`, `box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px var(--color-input-focus-ring)`
- **Filled**: `border-color: var(--color-input-filled-border)`
- **Error**: gradient border `linear-gradient(0deg, red-200, grey-150)` using padding-box/border-box technique (dark: red-800 → grey-600). The error selector targets both plain and filled cells to override the filled background. Shake animation (`acko-otp-shake 300ms ease-out`). Focus within error: `box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--color-error-ring, var(--color-error-subtle))`
- **Disabled**: `background: var(--color-input-disabled-bg)`, `border-color: var(--color-input-disabled-border)`, `color: var(--color-text-disabled)`

## Error gradient border technique

Uses double background with `padding-box` / `border-box` to achieve gradient border with rounded corners. The selector `.acko-otp-error .acko-otp-cell.acko-otp-cell-filled` ensures the error gradient overrides the filled state background:

```css
border: 1.5px solid transparent;
background:
  linear-gradient(var(--color-input-bg), var(--color-input-bg)) padding-box,
  linear-gradient(0deg, var(--red-200), var(--grey-150)) border-box;
```

Dark theme uses `red-800` → `grey-600` for the error gradient.
